---
title: French Onion Smothered Pork Chops with Mashed Potatoes & Green Beans
description: The star of this home-cooked show is the humble onion, needing only a little patience to coax out its rich savory-sweet flavor. Pile it atop juicy pan-seared pork chops, top with tangy Swiss cheese, and—voilà! French onion soup vibes galore. Serve with creamy mashed potatoes and roasted green beans, and you've got a luxe dinner—no restaurant required.

image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6716db47ffa4e28ccb95ebb3-787b9ba9.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6716db47ffa4e28ccb95ebb3-en-US.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 610 kcal
  fat: 32 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 46 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 490 mg
servings: 2
author: Sara Heilman
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/french-onion-smothered-pork-chops-6716db47ffa4e28ccb95ebb3
cuisine: North America
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1/2-inch pieces and place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Reserve 1/2 cup potato cooking liquid (3/4 cup for 4 servings), then drain. Return potatoes to #pot{} and mash with @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and @butter{1%tbsp} until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

While potatoes cook, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until green beans are browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}.

Pat @pork chops{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Return same pan to medium-high heat and add a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}. Add onion and half the @dried thyme{1%teaspoon}; cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is browned and softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Stir in @sugar{1%tsp} and a splash of water; cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is jammy, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once green beans are done, remove from oven and divide between plates; cover with foil to keep warm. Set oven to broil.

Place pork on baking sheet used for green beans; top with onion and @Swiss cheese{2%slices} (cutting slices to fit if needed). Broil until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Divide mashed potatoes and pork chops between plates with green beans. Serve.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.